  "prompt": "What is the legislative branch responsible for? What is the publication of the legislative branch?",
  "response": "The legislative branch is responsible for making and passing laws. In the United States, the legislative branch is comprised of two parts: the Senate and the House of Representatives, collectively known as Congress. Members of Congress propose bills, debate them, amend them, and vote on whether they should become law.\n\nThe primary publication of the legislative branch in the United States is the Congressional Record. This publication is the official record of the proceedings and debates of the United States Congress. It is published daily when Congress is in session and includes a transcript of speeches, debates, and votes held on the floor of both the House and the Senate.",
